{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-05-27T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"On World Otter Day, just look at this cutie swimming in the waters of Kachemak Bay, Alaska! Otters are captivating creatures that play an essential role in maintaining healthy ecosystems. Supported by the Otter Specialist Group (OSG)—a global network of professionals dedicated to the conservation of all 14 species—this day highlights the otter's vital contribution to nature. Known for their playful behaviour and remarkable intelligence, otters are key indicators of waterway health. Sadly, they face growing challenges from habitat loss and pollution.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.OtterDay_EN-IN4331346367_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.OtterDay_EN-IN4331346367_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"No 'otter' like them","Title":"Sea otter, Kachemak Bay, Homer, Alaska, United States","Copyright":"© roclwyr/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/59.725746,-151.141037/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=59.725746,-151.141037;S9;Kachemak Bay, Alaska, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260527_OtterDay\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Otter+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260526_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260527_OtterDay"},"Ssd":"20260527","Name":"OtterDay","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"4331346367","FullDateString":"27 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As spring sweeps across Northern California in the United States, the landscape is transformed by the vibrant displays of lupine flowers in shades of blue, purple and white. Flourishing in the region's Mediterranean climate, these wildflowers provide a vital source of nectar for pollinators such as bees, butterflies and beetles. With over 200 species found worldwide, lupines range from coastal varieties to those that thrive in mountain meadows. Beyond their striking beauty, lupines are essential to the ecosystem: by fixing nitrogen underground, they enrich soil fertility and support the growth of surrounding plants, even in nutrient-poor environments.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LupineBloom_EN-IN4015578692_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LupineBloom_EN-IN4015578692_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A season written in lupine","Title":"Lupine flowers in bloom, Northern California, United States","Copyright":"© Jeffrey Lewis/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"The name 'lupine' comes from the Latin word 'lupus,' meaning 'wolf.' It was once incorrectly believed that lupines 'wolfed' or depleted nutrients from the soil.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260526_LupineBloom\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lupinus&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260525_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260526_LupineBloom"},"Ssd":"20260526","Name":"LupineBloom","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"4015578692","FullDateString":"26 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What if a building could breathe? In the middle of Jaipur, Hawa Mahal does exactly that—pulling in air, pushing out heat and turning architecture into a quiet science experiment. It's less a palace, more a perfectly timed exhale. And yes, it really does live up to its name: the 'Palace of Winds.'","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.HawaMahal2026_EN-IN3702170011_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.HawaMahal2026_EN-IN3702170011_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A breeze in stone","Title":"View over Jaipur from Hawa Mahal, Rajasthan","Copyright":"© byheaven/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/26.92399,75.826668/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=26.92399,75.826668;S9;Hawa Mahal, Jaipur, Rajasthan&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260525_HawaMahal2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Hawa+Mahal&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260524_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260525_HawaMahal2026"},"Ssd":"20260525","Name":"HawaMahal2026","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"3702170011","FullDateString":"25 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The European Day of Parks celebrates protected areas across the continent, marking the creation of Europe's first national parks in 1909. It serves as a reminder that many of today's most iconic landscapes exist because of long-term conservation efforts. Today's image highlights a prime example of this legacy: Tre Cime Nature Park in northern Italy.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.DolomitesPark_EN-IN3505043244_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.DolomitesPark_EN-IN3505043244_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Preserving Europe's wild places","Title":"Tre Cime Nature Park, South Tyrol, Italy","Copyright":"© Adisorn Fineday Chutikunakorn/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/46.643931,12.343052/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=46.643931,12.343052;S9;Tre Cime Nature Park, Italy&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260524_DolomitesPark\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=European+Day+of+Parks&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260523_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260524_DolomitesPark"},"Ssd":"20260524","Name":"DolomitesPark","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"3505043244","FullDateString":"24 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Turtles are not only fascinating animals; they also play vital roles in nature. Sea turtles help keep seagrass beds and coral reefs healthy, while freshwater and land counterparts support balanced ecosystems. Their shells are part of their skeletons, formed from dozens of fused bones, and some species navigate using Earth's magnetic field to return to the beaches where they hatched.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ThreeTurtlesButterflies_EN-IN2942559231_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ThreeTurtlesButterflies_EN-IN2942559231_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Shell yeah, turtles!","Title":"Turtles with butterflies","Copyright":"© Patrick Gallet/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"There are seven species of marine turtles, and five are threatened with extinction.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260523_ThreeTurtlesButterflies\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Turtle+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260522_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260523_ThreeTurtlesButterflies"},"Ssd":"20260523","Name":"ThreeTurtlesButterflies","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2942559231","FullDateString":"23 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Observed each year on 22 May, International Day for Biological Diversity is a global reminder that life on Earth is richer—and more fragile—than it appears. Established by the United Nations, today highlights why protecting plants, animals and ecosystems matters for food, medicine, climate stability and everyday well-being.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.KauehiAtollLagoon_EN-IN0930317309_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.KauehiAtollLagoon_EN-IN0930317309_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"The shape of life at sea","Title":"Kauehi Atoll, Tuamotu Archipelago, French Polynesia","Copyright":"© WaterFrame_dpr/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-15.83333,-145.1167/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-15.83333,-145.1167;S9;Kauehi Atoll, Tuamotu Archipelago, French Polynesia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260522_KauehiAtollLagoon\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Day+for+Biological+Diversity&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260521_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260522_KauehiAtollLagoon"},"Ssd":"20260522","Name":"KauehiAtollLagoon","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"0930317309","FullDateString":"22 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"International Tea Day celebrates a drink that connects daily rituals to ancient landscapes. Just one look at the terraced tea fields of Sichuan Province, China, shows how deep those roots run. This misty region in southwest China is one of the earliest centres of tea culture, where people drank and cultivated tea more than 2,000 years ago. On nearby Mengding Mountain, a scholar named Wu Lizhen planted some of the world's first managed tea gardens during the Han Dynasty, laying the groundwork for generations of growers.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SichuanTea_EN-IN0699009240_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SichuanTea_EN-IN0699009240_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Brewing a legacy","Title":"Tea terraces in Sichuan Province, China","Copyright":"© lzf/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/30,103/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=30,103;S9;Sichuan, China&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260521_SichuanTea\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Tea+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260520_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260521_SichuanTea"},"Ssd":"20260521","Name":"SichuanTea","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"0699009240","FullDateString":"21 May, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Your average route to work might not resemble the one in today's image, but it shouldn't stop you from pedalling. World Bicycle Day invites us to rethink what's possible on two wheels—whether the ride cuts through city streets or remote terrain. Observed every 3 June, the United Nations–backed day recognises cycling as a practical way to move, supporting health, lowering emissions and making mobility more accessible.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BardenasReales_EN-IN2901722353_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BardenasReales_EN-IN2901722353_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Where the road stops, the ride begins","Title":"Cyclist in Bardenas Reales Natural Park and Biosphere Reserve, Navarra, Spain","Copyright":"© Artur Debat/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/42.210213,-1.515728/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=42.210213,-1.515728;S9;Las Bardenas Reales, Navarra, Spain&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260603_BardenasReales\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Bicycle+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260602_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260603_BardenasReales"},"Ssd":"20260603","Name":"BardenasReales","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2901722353","FullDateString":"3 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At midnight, a map shifted—and a region found its rhythm. On 2 June 2014, Telangana became India's youngest state, carved from Andhra Pradesh, with Hyderabad as its capital. Telangana Day marks that moment—and the momentum since.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TelanganaDay2026_EN-IN2729505086_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TelanganaDay2026_EN-IN2729505086_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Making a state-ment","Title":"Minarets of Charminar, Hyderabad, Telangana","Copyright":"© RAJARSHI SENGUPTA/iStock/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/17.36157,78.474663/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=17.36157,78.474663;S9;Charminar, Hyderabad, Telangana&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260602_TelanganaDay2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Telangana+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260601_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260602_TelanganaDay2026"},"Ssd":"20260602","Name":"TelanganaDay2026","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2729505086","FullDateString":"2 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Palermo, the capital of the island of Sicily in southern Italy, is a city where layers of history, art and culture meet in a vivid and sometimes chaotic harmony. Founded by the Phoenicians and later shaped by Romans, Arabs, Normans and Spaniards, it carries traces of many civilisations that passed through the Mediterranean. This rich past is visible in its architecture, from the Arab-Norman palaces and churches recognised by UNESCO to the Baroque facades that define its historic streets.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.OlivaPalermo_EN-IN8542997213_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.OlivaPalermo_EN-IN8542997213_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Flavours of history","Title":"Palermo skyline, Sicily, Italy","Copyright":"© Sean Pavone/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/38.121254,13.359494/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=38.121254,13.359494;S9;Palermo, Sicily, Italy&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260601_OlivaPalermo\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Palermo&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260531_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260601_OlivaPalermo"},"Ssd":"20260601","Name":"OlivaPalermo","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"8542997213","FullDateString":"1 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Cutting a surreal path through the high-altitude deserts of western China, Xitai Jinaier Lake (also known as West Taijinar Lake) is a striking salt lake in the remote Qaidam Basin. A stretch of National Highway 315 runs directly across its shallow waters, creating the illusion of a road floating between two worlds. On one side, the water often appears deep blue; on the other, a softer green hue, a contrast shaped by differing mineral concentrations in the brine.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Qinghai_EN-IN1637121010_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Qinghai_EN-IN1637121010_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Between the blues","Title":"Highway through Xitai Jinaier Lake, Qinghai Province, China","Copyright":"© Kaicheng Xu/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/35.668594,96.043144/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=35.668594,96.043144;S9;Qinghai Province, China&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260531_Qinghai\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Qaidam+Basin+China&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260530_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260531_Qinghai"},"Ssd":"20260531","Name":"Qinghai","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"1637121010","FullDateString":"31 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Etosha National Park, Namibia, is not a place for soft starts, and the plains zebra foal in this image seems to get the memo. In a land this vast—nearly 22,300 square kilometres of salt pans and grassland—timing is everything, and hesitation is expensive. Lions, spotted hyenas, wild dogs, cheetahs and leopards constantly pressure the herd—especially the youngest—so zebras are born ready. Minutes after arrival, they're upright. Hours later, they're moving.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.EquusQuagga_EN-IN1397641014_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.EquusQuagga_EN-IN1397641014_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Reading between the lines","Title":"Plains zebra foal in Etosha National Park, Namibia","Copyright":"© Sharon Heald/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-18.98073,15.762634/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-18.98073,15.762634;S9;Etosha National Park, Namibia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260530_EquusQuagga\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Plains+zebras&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260529_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260530_EquusQuagga"},"Ssd":"20260530","Name":"EquusQuagga","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"1397641014","FullDateString":"30 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"In Sagarmatha National Park, Nepal, Mount Everest rises into view, calm and unmoved as evening settles in. But on 29 May, 1953, that stillness was broken. After years of planning and weeks of climbing, New Zealander Edmund Hillary and Sherpa mountaineer Tenzing Norgay reached the summit. At more than 8,800 metres above sea level, they became the first people known to have stood at Earth's highest point.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SummitEverest_EN-IN1233380057_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SummitEverest_EN-IN1233380057_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A 'peak' into history","Title":"Mount Everest summit, Sagarmatha National Park, Nepal","Copyright":"© fotoVoyager/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/27.980471,86.880623/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=27.980471,86.880623;S9;Mount Everest, Sagarmatha National Park, Solukhumbu District, Nepal&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260529_SummitEverest\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Mt+Everest+summit+1953&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260528_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260529_SummitEverest"},"Ssd":"20260529","Name":"SummitEverest","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"1233380057","FullDateString":"29 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As night settles over Suwon, South Korea, the old city wall pictured here shows that function doesn't necessarily cancel out beauty—it can create it. Built between 1794 and 1796 under King Jeongjo of the Joseon Dynasty, Hwaseong Fortress was more than a barrier. It was policy in stone: a reform-minded push for a leaner, better-run state, driven by practicality and a deeply personal motive. Jeongjo ordered its construction to honour his father while strengthening a kingdom that wanted smarter systems, not just thicker walls.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.HwaesongFortress_EN-IN3146231102_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.HwaesongFortress_EN-IN3146231102_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Design meets discipline","Title":"Old city wall of Hwaseong Fortress, Suwon, South Korea","Copyright":"© aomam/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/37.289031,127.014114/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=37.289031,127.014114;S9